  "text": "The MDL principle is a practical realization of Occam's razor [CITATION_1] and seeks for a model with a short description, which also yields compact and well behaved data. This compression of data finds applications in various branches of statistics and machine learning such as statistical inference [CITATION_2] , unsupervised learning [CITATION_3] , Bayesian model selection [CITATION_4] , and causal inference [CITATION_5] . The information content of dynamical systems is investigated in [CITATION_6] , [CITATION_7] .",
